mary_text\",\"text\":\"**Enhancing test coverage**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the repeated read/write processes with standard streams and nested objects. There might be coverage gaps after the native tests, possibly due to previous failures related to UID. It seems like I need to add more tests to address this. I can modify the tests to incorporate a nested envelope and tracking while ensuring a one-to-one file structure. I should also determine the current source file to see if there's anything existing that I can build upon.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_sz4TT4NXuzrtvOwAReSDzcjp|fc_00c5cc8b9a72fe1d016a25fc6bab4481938604d317b2ed2c40", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/build/reports/jacoco -type f | sort | head -20 && find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/build/reports/jacoco -type f -name '*.xml' -maxdepth 5 -print"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4623, "output": 1311, "cacheRead": 53760, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59694, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780874315896, "responseId": "resp_00c5cc8b9a72fe1d016a25fc4cc030819397f55da37e80e95e"}}
