[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring serialization challenges**\n\nI'm considering using a helper for generating an `ObjectOutputStream` with a write descriptor replacement, but it might require manual building by subclassing. Java protocols can be complex for handling `BigInteger`. The initial stream might not cover dynamic agents since deserialization only uses `JCE readObject`, which seems limited. Perhaps I can add tests with subclasses to assert internal big integers. I should also consider testing serialization and deserialization of a private key within a `Serializable` envelope for better recognition by the native agent.\n\n**Enhancing test coverage**\n\nI'm thinking about the repeated read/write processes with standard streams and nested objects. There might be coverage gaps after the native tests, possibly due to previous failures related to UID. It seems like I need to add more tests to address this. I can modify the tests to incorporate a nested envelope and tracking while ensuring a one-to-one file structure. I should also determine the current source file to see if there's anything existing that I can build upon.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00c5cc8b9a72fe1d016a25fc4d8ba48193ad911b9aa0e1093a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJfxrE9RG1yqjm6nTtSw15FfzDqUG8lalGfaeGpNBjuOcyjJYN3eEkgQAylEg4bkbnuIk0z_iSYaVnfkQptlAfu3HirG3KW4X0Z-Err5SKyf8nPEDUgkoeOzhxvn2O5Bp43dqaEp2IVvZFIGZMQ1IhGAB_txI3jsXZyTk9Z__ZHHvb5SlrEY1rFawoCGHB1PuCLQHCX8jclwaBHG1w4dlpPLUXRz9hO1HRUf1Ch45z4k0K9ut1spAOiKn3cyLPJkZksMRJzeGXSeSdryC3TqxPywqV5gnDAe89a9vjHQK7fYf7Ga9qGzGToahPZ4NY-XG9wUZCo3T3V0TJQ3l-Z9NELHdQy2bSWgW2PSmRuxeRMa7FTO0OYlzebYUICnN01GOQllW4jtrI3nZCFc1C7JCEEjS1See5ZNFF4djSkGINZxdSpMK-f100MVPFqZ59uAN_4vwf5LOGl_WfpW-rO8Zc_ww3wWYCISzZXorJtP3C8cY1oL9vrz14yIK8QvJnD-iguMUr6mPD5-NxAS2Dab1ql89R8hIX7Fu6BfMjm8vU7pq-aPkbaiaOnkYYPB1T4AeQwPNJw05tjQLKAYCwZKrIVnmyKa56Ukp5vTQO